snippet.title: Johnny Depp & Amber Heard Controversy Coming To An End
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp & Amber Heard Controversy Coming To An End
‚úÖ Subscribe to us ‚Üí https://www.youtube.com/c/FilmRoyalty?sub_confirmation=1
üîî Turn on notifications to never miss a new upload!
‚úÖ  Follow us on Instagram ‚Üí https://www.instagram.com/filmroyalty

About:
Four years later the couple were back in court, but this time in London. However, this was not Amber Heard's case - she had not chosen to be here. This was a libel action Depp had brought against a British newspaper, The Sun. At the heart of the case was his assertion that the allegations of physical abuse were an "elaborate hoax". Depp employed one of the best-known libel barristers in the country to try to prove the claims were untrue.
Over the next three weeks, Heard arrived at court each day and walked past her former husband's fans, who were convinced that it was their hero who was the victim and it was she who had assaulted him. In court her story, photos, memories and the accounts of her friends were all exposed to the world and said by Depp's team and supporters to be part of a plot to falsely prove that he was, as The Sun had claimed in April 2018, a "wife beater".

It was not just the fans and media who were watching carefully. Lawyers were already wondering, if he won, what impact this would have on women coming forward with claims of domestic violence. Outside, Johnny Depp would arrive each day to cheers. But his behaviour and lifestyle were also under the microscope - and a judge has now ruled that The Sun's allegations were "substantially true".

snippet.title: Jason Momoa Says HE HATES Working With Amber Heard!!! (IG LIVE)
snippet.description:
Jason Momoa Tells Fans The Onset Relationship Between Him and Amber Heard On Instagram Live!!

Subscribe to The Spotlight üëâ  https://bit.ly/3txAgy1

WATCH NEXT: ‚ñ∂Ô∏è

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6vH_1E0jJN8&t=22s

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YVPyBraRags&t=12s

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZJawm0jcmY8&t=2s

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RELATED VIDEOS:üëá

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Jka1JsBBmCU

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ShObyc9vqXM&t=96s

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g7QY3uedq5k


Whereas, the once-famous actress is having a difficult time coping and contacting many of the Hollywood stars including one of her close friends Jason Momoa. Yes, mate it is what it is...

The Aquaman star, Jason eventually opened up on his relationship with Amber Heard and what he feels about her. Well, we all know how fun and interesting the kind of a guy Jason Momoa is. Jason is everyone's favourite (laughing)

Adding on a valuable tip for you, try to stay calm and patient around him, Jason really can't see anyone sitting calm, he's a real attention seeker. If the word "attention seeker" is given to someone ever in the future, I would request the officials to kindly give it to Jason Momoa. , 

Well as I already mentioned, Jason would never attempt any prank that can harm a person in any way. We must just agree that we adore and love him a lot. And on the other hand, Jason never forgets to charm ladies, with his hot looks and of course beautiful smile. Who called him Jason Momoa and not Jason the charmer? (laughing)
Speaking about Jason Momoa's and Amber Heard's bond, they really get along well together, but as you all know things never stay the same. Jason's and Amber's friendship bond was affected after Jason decided to play a master prank on Amber Heard.

Once while shooting for Aquaman, the charming yet playful Star  Jason Momoa, played a sick prank on Amber heard. Well, what he did was truly sad and tragic. It's like you have made a sandhill and out of nowhere a random person comes and destroys your sandhill. Did you feel that pain now?

Well, Jason didn't ruin Amber Heard's Sandhill (laughs jokingly) but did something the same that left Amber Heard sad all day long. Let me break this down for you, The Game of Thrones star, intentionally in the name of prank, tore the last ten pages of Amber Heard books that she regularly used to read in between shots and takes... Like, yes!!!

Shockingly Jason did that, I don't know why that doesn't sound like a Big deal to him, but it is...And guess what? Amber's a bookworm (oops Jason, you shouldn't have done that) But what's done is done (laughing nervously) We feel you, Amber!!

Amber Heard shared all the incident, where Jason went to keep her attention on set, she confessed, " I love Jason we had so much fun together but he is allergic to being ignored and I'm a bookworm who loves to read the books, he adopted this method of ripping out the pages of my book so I would pay attention to him". Poor Amber...

Whereas, the crew staff was helpful to Amber Heard, due to Jason's book ripping pranks the crew on the set of Aquaman designed a book bag out of green screen material so that Amber could carry her books on set with her and read between takes.

"I would feel so bad if someone was going out of  their way to throw her book to her but they could tell I was going crazy so the wardrobe built me a book bag" Amber stated in the interview with Good Morning America..."

Delving into the history, Amber Heard's personal life problem which is no more limited to her speaks a lot about her behaviour and the kind of a person she is. As we all know that Amber Heard and Johnny Depp are hooked into the legal drama, things seem to slip out of Dear Amber's hand. 

Talking about the legal drama, the case eventually took a u-turn resulting in a case favouring Johnny Depp. The recent leaked audio call and bodycam footage revealed the true colours of Aquaman star Amber Heard. Accepting the fact that Johnny Depp was never the abuser it was Amber Heard who physically abused Johnny Depp celebrity news clevver news entertainment news information overload inform overload johnny depp appeal amber heard aquaman 2 informoverload amber heard petition

However, the Warner brothers never reacted to the demand of fans, asking to kick out Amber Heard from the Aquaman 2, while they had already kicked Johnny out of 'the pirates of Caribbean series. 

Johnny Depp fans tweeted in his favour and asked that Heard should be fired from Aquaman 2. While one of Johnny's fans tweeted writing " I don't understand why Warner brothers fired Johnny Depp but not Amber Heard, they both have evidence of being abused by each other, and abusive women are rarely held to the same standard as abusive men".

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard back in court for day two of trial over 'wife beater' article
snippet.description:
Subscribe to the Evening Standard on YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC7RQon_YwCnp_LbPtEwW65w?sub_confirmation=1

Johnny Depp and Amber Heard both waved as they arrived at the High Court on Wednesday ahead of the second day of the trial.

Mr Depp, who says he follows a Southern Gentleman code, is suing The Sun for libel after being dubbed a ‚Äúwife beater‚Äù in a 2018 article, and denies ever being violent towards Ms Heard during their volatile marriage.

He in turn claims that Ms Heard was the violent abuser, insisting she had married him to further her career and called the actress a ‚Äúsociopath‚Äù. She denies his allegations.

snippet.description:
Johnny Depp has reportedly accused ex-wife Amber Heard of lying about giving her divorce settlement away to charity. After the exes' finalized their split, Heard pledged to keep none of the $7 million settlement and instead split it between two charities, the ACLU and Children's Hospital of Los Angeles. According to a new report from the Daily Mail, Depp's lawyers claim that Heard‚Äôs pledge was a ‚Äúsham‚Äù and that documents obtained by subpoena from Children‚Äôs Hospital Los Angeles are a ‚Äúsmoking gun.‚Äù A lawyer for Heard asserted that the actress intended to fulfill her pledge and had only been ‚Äúdelayed in that goal‚Äù because she‚Äôs ‚Äúbeen forced to spend millions of dollars defending‚Äù herself amid Depp‚Äôs multiple lawsuits.

snippet.title: Day Seven: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard arrive at the High Court
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp's ex-fiancee Winona Ryder is set to appear at the High Court in London today in support of the actor's sensational libel claim against a newspaper over an article that labelled him a 'wife beater'. Depp is suing The Sun's publisher News Group Newspapers (NGN) and its executive editor Dan Wootton over an April 2018 article which alleged he was violent towards ex-wife Amber Heard during their tumultuous relationship. Stranger Things actress Ryder, 48, who had a relationship with Depp, 57, in the 1990s, will give evidence in support of the actor's case over a video link from Los Angeles this afternoon. Also today, the court is due to hear from actress and advocate for the #MeToo movement Katherine Kendall, who claims she was 'misquoted' in The Sun's article. In the left photograph, Heard is front centre with her girlfriend Bianca Butti, her lawyer Jennifer Robinson and her sister Whitney Heard.

snippet.title: Johnny Depp‚Äôs tight-knit birth family
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp is definitely the alive legend of Hollywood cinematography and the sex symbol of present days. He is not just an attractive man, but also a super-talented actor, who gave an outstanding contribution to modern entertainment industry. The characters, played by Depp, are really versatile and deep personalities. 

Actually, he started his career as a member of a music band. The Sleepy Hollow start was really passionate about music ‚Äì he could spend all day long playing the guitar. However, later, he was introduced to Nicolas Cage, who advised Johnny to try himself in acting. 

Well, let‚Äôs have a look at people, who surrounded the future movie star, while he was a child.

John Christopher Depp, the father of the Edward Scissorhands, worked as a civil engineer. Due to Johnny‚Äôs father‚Äôs job the family had to move a lot. Finally, when Captain Jack Sparrow was seven, they settled in Florida. When the future star was only fifteen his parents divorced. This created emotional distance between father and son. 

Betty Sue Palmer, Johnny‚Äôs mother, was a waitress and a parent to four kids. After the divorce, Betty married once again to Robert Palmer. When Depp was 12, she presented him with his first guitar. Deborah J Depp is a younger Daniel‚Äôs sister, who was also adopted by Johnny‚Äôs father. Debbie is an elementary school teacher from Lexington, where she resides with her husband and two children. 

Eliza Christi Depp-Dembrowski is three years older than her famous brother. She manages Infinitum Nihil ‚Äì Depp‚Äôs film production company and is a mother of four kids. Eliza is really close with her starry brother and gives him great assistance in his business dealings.

snippet.title: Amber Heard's coming out struggle | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
The 32-year-old actress identifies as bisexual and has said that telling her parents she was in a relationship with a woman for the first time wasn't easy, because of their "religious" background.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Amber Heard's parents "didn't know how to process" things when she told them she was bisexual.

The 32-year-old actress identifies as bisexual and has said that telling her parents she was in a relationship with a woman for the first time wasn't easy, because of their "religious" background.

She said: "I am from Austin, Texas. My dad is out of central casting Texan. Good Southern man, and I was raised in a religious home. And being an outspoken lesbian, atheist, vegetarian, I remember when I told them about my relationship, that I was in love with this woman, and at the beginning of that it was just tears, tears.‚Äù

But the 'Aquaman' star says that while her parents didn't understand her sexuality at first, their "attitudes and hearts" changed over time.

Speaking during a panel at SXSW, she added that five years later, she was getting an award and had asked her parents to drive out to Dallas.

Upon collecting her award, she said she could ‚Äúsee them sitting front and center and here I am getting this 'gay' award... My parents in five years, look at the journey. Attitudes and hearts can change."

snippet.title: Amber Heard Mother Died At 64 | THE DAILY NEWS
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Mother Died At 64 | THE DAILY NEWS
Amber Heard is mourning the death of her mother.

On Sunday, the Aquaman actress, 34, revealed that her mom, Paige died, paying tribute to her loved one with a heartfelt post on Instagram. Sharing a pair of throwback photos of herself with her mother, Heard wrote that she is "heartbroken and devastated beyond belief."

"She left us too early, clasping onto the memory of her beautiful, gentle soul," she wrote. "She will be missed from the very depths of our hearts forever."

Heard said she feels "truly lucky" to be her mother's daughter, while also thanking everyone for their "kindness, support and generosity," which she said has been "utterly soul-saving."

"Her unflinching, open heart made her the most beautiful woman I had ever known," wrote the actress. "It‚Äôs hard to imagine and even more difficult to say but I feel truly lucky to have been her daughter and been given the gift of having the light she shone on everyone, fall on me for nearly 34 years."

She added: "This has been an unbelievably painful time but in that, I am reminded of what survives us all, love."

snippet.title: Amber Heard Fined $7,000 for Skipping Deposition | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
Amber Heard has been fined almost $7,000 for skipping a deposition in her ongoing legal dispute with a producer.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Amber Heard had herself a bit of legal trouble, and it‚Äôs going to cost her.

The actress was fined almost seven thousand dollars for skipping a deposition in her ongoing legal dispute with a producer.

Yep, a judge ordered Heard to make the payment of $6,850 - much less than the $70,000 the producer was asking for.

Amber was set to give a deposition in October in the legal proceedings to determine if she bailed on her obligations to promote the film, London Fields.

The producer says she breached contract and sabotaged his movie by refusing to film scenes and do publicity‚Ä¶ Amber on the other hand says she was a victim of sexploitation, even countersuing, accusing the producer of breaking her nudity clause by secretly using a body double to film an explicit pornographic sex scene.

And according to Amber, all this was done to trick to audience into thinking she had done the scene.

The film is based on the 1989 novel and centers around a clairvoyant femme fatale who has a premonition of her impending murder.

snippet.title: Did Amber Heard, Elon Musk just confirm their relationship? - ANI News
snippet.description:
New Delhi, Apr 25 (ANI): It seems Amber Heard and Elon Musk are more than just a fling. Amber Heard made the couple`s romance official by sharing a photo on Instagram of herself resting her arm against Musk. The 31-year-old-actress captioned the snap, "Cheeky." The photo also shows a kiss-mark on Musk's right cheek, which is clearly visible. Earlier, the 'Danish Girl' star and Tesla founder were spotted together for the first time in public while in Australia, where the actress is currently filming her upcoming movie 'Aquaman,' according to People Magazine. The couple spent Sunday at the Gold Coast's Currumbin Wildlife Sanctuary, where they walked arm-in-arm through the reserve. Amber Heard filed for divorce from Johnny Depp in last May and their divorce was finalised in January 2017, whereas Elon Musk filed for divorce from wife Talulah Riley in January 2015 and has five sons from previous marriage.

snippet.title: 'He's nuts mom': Amber Heard shared fears about Johnny Depp in 2013 | ABC News
snippet.description:
Actor Amber Heard texted her mother in 2013 that she was heartbroken to discover her then boyfriend, Johnny Depp, became violent and abusive when high on drugs and alcohol, likening him to Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde.

The texts were read to the High Court in London, where Ms Heard was giving evidence on behalf of the publishers of tabloid newspaper The Sun, who are being sued for defamation by Mr Depp over a 2018 article that labelled him a "wife beater".

Mr Depp, who gave evidence last week, denies all of Ms Heard's allegations of violence and abuse and says she assaulted him.

"He's nuts mom. Violent and crazy. I am heartbroken that THIS is who I love," Ms Heard said in one of a series of texts she sent to her mother on a single day in March 2013, which were read out by a lawyer.

According to Ms Heard, Mr Depp had been up all night snorting cocaine and drinking whisky when he turned violent after becoming enraged by the sight of a painting by her former partner, Tasya van Ree, hanging on the wall of her apartment.

Read more here: https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-07-24/hes-nuts-mom-heard-shared-fears-about-depp-in-2013/12487620

snippet.title: Johnny Depp, Amber Heard finalise divorce - ANI News
snippet.description:
New Delhi, Jan 15 (ANI): Looks like Johnny Depp and Amber Heard are finally turning a new leaf regarding their turbulent divorce process. Amber had earlier filed for papers to end their 15-month union in May 2016 and at a recent hearing, which neither she nor Depp attended, a judge signed papers to finalise their divorce, reports E! Online. Reportedly, the judge also denied a notion the 'Black Mass' actor's attorney had filed to have Heard pay the actor's attorney fees. This news comes about five months after the former couple reached a settlement. Heard's attorney was quoted as saying, "It is a great day. All Amber wanted was a divorce and now she has it. In the words of Gerald Ford, 'Our long national nightmare is over."

snippet.title: Amber Heard says Jason Momoa's pranks drove her crazy | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
The 32-year-old actress and Jason had "so much fun" during the 'Aquaman' shoot, but she also found his demand for attention to be tiring at times.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Amber Heard admits Jason Momoa's pranks drove her "crazy" while they were filming 'Aquaman'.

The 32-year-old actress and Jason had "so much fun" during the 'Aquaman' shoot, but she also found his demand for attention to be tiring at times.

Amber told 'Good Morning America': "We have so much fun together, but he is allergic to being ignored. I'm a bookworm. I love to read, so whenever there's a break on set, I like to read. He quickly learned ... so he ripped out the pages of my book so I'd pay attention to him, and it would drive me crazy because I'd have 30 pages left and they'd be gone."

Amber also revealed that because the crew knew how much she loved to read between takes they made her a special book bag out of her costume material so she could have her novels within easy reach.

The Hollywood star gushed: "Wardrobe made me a book bag built out of the green screen material so that I could sling it over me and carry it around and bring out my book."

snippet.description:
https://erena.org/
Radio Erena (‚ÄúOur Eritrea‚Äù), a Tigrinya and Arabic language station broadcasting by satellite to Eritrea, began operating on June 15, 2009, in Paris, five days ahead of World Refugee Day. The result of an initiative by Eritrean journalists based abroad and supported by Reporters Without Borders, the station is offering freely-reported, independent news and information to Eritreans in Eritrea.

Independent of any political organisation or government, Radio Erena is offering news, cultural programmes, music and entertainment. A network of contributors based all over the world is providing the Paris-based staff with Tigrinya and arabic language programmes that are broadcast via NileSat.

Eritreans can tune into Radio Erena on the 11678 Mhz frequency with vertical polarisation (SR 27500, FEC 3/4).

Eritrea has had no free press since September 2001, when the few Asmara-based independent newspapers were closed down and their publishers and editors were arrested as part of a wave of round-ups ordered by President Issaias Afeworki.

Since then, the only news available to Eritreans in their national language has been provided by the state media ‚Äì Eri-TV, Radio Dimtsi Hafash and the government daily Hadas Eritrea ‚Äì which are all closely supervised by the information ministry.

Africa‚Äôs biggest prison for journalists, Eritrea has for the past two years been ranked last in the Reporters Without Borders index that measures the degree of respect for press freedom in a total of 173 countries.

You can contact Radio ERENA‚Äôs newsroom by telephone : +33 (0)1 45 89 64 51

Or by email :  radioerena@gmail.com

snippet.title: Johnny Depp claims Amber Heard punched him | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
Johnny Depp has alleged his ex-wife Amber Heard "punched him twice in the face" when they were still married.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Johnny Depp has alleged his ex-wife Amber Heard "punched him twice in the face" when they were still married.

The 55-year-old actor and the 'Aquaman' star were married for two years from 2015 to 2017 and underwent a turbulent divorce procedure which saw Amber accuse Johnny of being "verbally and physically abusive" throughout their relationship.

But now, as part of a libel case in the UK, the 'Pirates of the Caribbean' actor has claimed Amber physically assaulted him after he arrived two hours late to her 30th birthday party in 2016.

In court documents obtained by People, Johnny alleges that Amber, was "cold towards" him and began "criticising" him after the guests had left.

Johnny claims he was sober when the alleged incident took place, and that Amber ‚Äì who he says had been drinking - became "aggressive and violent, punching him twice in the face."

snippet.title: The O variant
snippet.description:
Worst ever Covid variant? Omicron 

B.1.1.529 

Increased contagion

Immune escape

Sicker people

WHO, VOC

https://www.who.int/news/item/26-11-2021-classification-of-omicron-(b.1.1.529)-sars-cov-2-variant-of-concern
The Technical Advisory Group on SARS-CoV-2 Virus Evolution
Independent group of experts
First reported to WHO from South Africa on 24th November 2021
South Africa, infections have increased steeply, coinciding with the detection of B.1.1.529 variant
The first known confirmed B.1.1.529 infection was from a specimen collected on 9th November 2021 
Preliminary evidence suggests an increased risk of reinfection with this variant
The number of cases of this variant appears to be increasing in almost all provinces in South Africa
Current SARS-CoV-2 PCR diagnostics continue to detect this variant. 
For one widely used PCR test, one of the three target genes is not detected
(called S gene dropout or S gene target failure)
This variant may have a growth advantage.

How did the new variant develop?

https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-021-03552-w

Professor Francois Balloux, Computational Biology Systems, University College London

Mutated during a chronic infection of a person whose immune system was already weakened by an untreated HIV/Aids infection

Botswana

Discovered, November 11th (collected 9th) 2021 in Botswana

South Africa

77 confirmed cases

90% of new cases in Gauteng, probably B.1.1.529

Early signs of rapid spread in Gauteng province, 900 cases per day

May have spread to eight other provinces in South Africa

SA, fully vaccinated, 24%

Israel

https://www.telegraph.co.uk/global-health/science-and-disease/new-coronavirus-variant-reason-concern-say-researchers/?li_source=LI&li_medium=liftigniter-onward-journey

1 returnee from Malawi

Two other people suspected of having the variant are also in quarantine

All three were fully vaccinated

Prime Minister Naftali Bennett
 
We are currently on the verge of a state of emergency

Belgium

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OfwoROrBiVE

1 case 

Came from Egypt to Belgium on November 11th 

First symptoms on November 22nd 

Hong Kong

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hm-WzJ0KR0M

Two cases, from next door in quarantine hotel

Traveller from SA

Penny Moore, virologist, University of Witwatersrand, Johannesburg

https://www.theguardian.com/world/2021/nov/25/what-do-we-know-about-the-new-worst-ever-covid-variant

Breakthrough infections have been reported following,

Johnson & Johnson, Pfizer-BioNtech, Oxford-AstraZeneca

R = 2 so far

SA, National Institute for Communicable Diseases

Cases, + 2,465 (nearly double yesterdays)

32 mutations in the spike protein

10 on RBD

(Delta variant has 8 mutations)

Beta (SA) variant has 3

Younger people appear to be contracting and spreading

BioNTech-Pfizer need two weeks to assess new variant's impact

Would need two weeks at most to assess how well its coronavirus vaccine works against B.1.1.529 

may require an adjustment of our vaccine if the variant spreads globally

Global spread

WHO advises risk-based, scientific approach to travel restrictions

risk-based and scientific approach to travel restrictions

WHO spokesman Christian Lindmeier 

At this point, implementing travel restrictions is being cautioned against

UK flight bans so far

700 arrivals per day to UK from SA

South Africa, Namibia, Lesotho, Botswana, Eswatini,  Zimbabwe

Recent arrivals from southern Africa will also tracked down and offered tests

Germany, Italy, Israel, Kenya, Singapore, Japan, France, Bahrain, Czech Republic have also suspended flights

European Commission, called on members to ban flights

Sajid Javid

very live discussions about adding to the red list

Professor Danny Altmann, immunologist Imperial College

We thought delta was the dominant variant and nothing could displace it ‚Äì 

this looks potentially horrible enough to displace it, if it is allowed to spread.
 
We have all become pandemic fatigued, yet if this was a report of a terrorist threat, we would now be raising the threat level from amber to red. 

Professor Madhukar Pai, global health, McGill University

This is what happens when we leave three billion plus people unvaccinated

Vaccines can be tweaked if needed

Dr Anthony Fauci

Flight ban possible

We need to get the facts

no indication it has yet reached the US

New variant is a red flag

Until it's properly tested... we don't know whether or not it evades the antibodies that protect you against the virus

Angelique Coetzee, South African Medical Association

For now, it is a storm in a tea cup

https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-59426277

Peter Horby, Professor of Emerging Infectious Diseases, University of Oxford

many red flags - more than we would've expected or ever planned for

snippet.title: Amber Heard donates divorce settlement to charity | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
The Children's Hospital Los Angeles has confirmed that Amber Heard did donate part of her divorce settlement to the charity after promising that she would following her split from Johnny Depp.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

The Children's Hospital Los Angeles (CHLA) has confirmed that Amber Heard did donate part of her divorce settlement to the charity after promising that she would following her split from Johnny Depp.

The 31-year-old actress divorced Johnny in 2016 and won a whopping $7 million in her settlement, which she promised she would split between two charities, American Civil Liberties Union, and CHLA.

And now, CHLA have published a report for 2017 which listed "Ms. Amber Heard" on its "Honor Roll of Donors", which indicated she had donated an undisclosed amount within the bracket of $1 million to $5 million.

Amber and Johnny, released a joint statement after reaching their divorce settlement in August 2016 in which it was stated Amber would be making the charitable donation.

Good for you Amber!

snippet.title: Amber Heard felt ‚Äúsuperhuman‚Äù on 'Aquaman' set | Daily Celebrity News | Splash TV
snippet.description:
The 32-year-old actress really enjoyed the preparation for her role as Mera in the upcoming movie, even if it meant training six days a week.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Amber Heard felt "pretty superhuman" on the set of 'Aquaman'.

The 32-year-old actress really enjoyed the preparation for her role as Mera in the upcoming movie, even if it meant training six days a week.

She said: "After four and a half months of training six days a week, you feel pretty superhuman."

Whilst her co-star Jason Momoa added to Entertainment Tonight: "Your body is constantly working. You're doing judo, jiu-jitsu, fight choreography."

Meanwhile, Amber previously revealed she was delighted with her first encounter with her character, who joins Aquaman to help keep the peace between the seven seas and the surface world.

And when Amber was offered the role, she didn't expect a superhero movie would resonate with her "core principles" until the role of a "badass warrior queen" was pitched to her.

SUBSCRIBE NOW : https://goo.gl/JaLP0U

Johnny Depp and Amber Heard's marriage reportedly reached its end after an argument over faeces left in their bed.

The 32-year-old actress and her friends have reportedly been accused by Johnny of leaving the faeces as a "prank" to get back at him for turning up late to her 30th birthday bash in the April 2016.

A source close to the 55-year-old actor has alleged there is "strong, photographic evidence that connected Amber to the faeces".

It's reported that the 'Pirates of the Caribbean' star's housekeeper found the faeces and told the actor it looked too big to not be a human's.

However, a spokesperson for the actress has denied this, claiming it was simply their dog Boo who had left the surprise as the pooch has "bowel control issues".

snippet.title: Johnny Depp and Amber Heard Arrive for Final Day of Libel Trial
snippet.description:
Actor Johnny Depp and Actress Amber Heard arrive at Britain‚Äôs Royal Courts of Justice for the final day of Depp‚Äôs libel case against New Group Newspapers, Tuesday, July 28.
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî 
READ MORE: A lawyer for British tabloid The Sun said Monday that Johnny Depp abused Amber Heard during their relationship, committing acts of violence fueled by misogyny and unleashed by addiction to alcohol and drugs.
 
Attorney Sasha Wass was summing up at Depp's libel case against the newspaper over an article alleging he physically abused ex-wife Heard ‚Äî a high-stakes celebrity trial in which the reputations of both former spouses are at stake.
 
Depp is suing News Group Newspapers, publisher of The Sun, and the newspaper's executive editor, Dan Wootton, at the High Court in London over an April 2018 article, which called him a "wife-beater." He strongly denies being violent to Heard.
 
The case is due to end Tuesday, but judge Andrew Nicol is not expected to deliver his ruling for several weeks.
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Attorney Sasha Wass was summing up at Depp's libel case against the newspaper over an article alleging he physically abused ex-wife Heard ‚Äî a high-stakes celebrity trial in which the reputations of both former spouses are at stake.
 
Depp is suing News Group Newspapers, publisher of The Sun, and the newspaper's executive editor, Dan Wootton, at the High Court in London over an April 2018 article, which called him a "wife-beater." He strongly denies being violent to Heard.
 
The case is due to end Tuesday, but judge Andrew Nicol is not expected to deliver his ruling for several weeks.

This is one of the most tiring legal battles in the Hollywood history! Johnny Depp and Amber Heard have been fighting over 4 years now. However, it is already can be said that there is a slow progress in this case and it becomes clear that Johnny Depp will get the justice he deserves any time soon. The case is still going on in the US and so far, the judges are presiding over the suit are ruling in favor of Johnny Depp. With all the new evidence coming up, it is clear that Amber Heard might lose the legal battle and to avoid that Amber Heard‚Äôs lawyers have tried everything to get the court to toss out the defamation suit and adopt the ruling of the UK libel case.
We all know that it's a really difficult battle for Johnny Depp and that the consequences are really dramatic for him, because he lost so many roles and Hollywood started boycotting him. JD even spoke up about cancel culture recently and said that he is a victim of cancel culture and that ‚Äúno one is safe‚Äù from the movement, calling on people to ‚Äústand up‚Äù for people facing ‚Äúinjustice‚Äù.
‚ÄúIt can be seen as an event in history that lasted for however long it lasted, this cancel culture, this instant rush to judgement based on what essentially amounts to polluted air,‚Äù he commented ahead of receiving the honorary Donostia Award at this year‚Äôs San Sebastian Film Festival.
‚ÄúIt‚Äôs so far out of hand now that I can promise you that no one is safe. Not one of you. No one out that door. No one is safe,‚Äù he continued. ‚ÄúIt takes one sentence and there‚Äôs no more ground, the carpet has been pulled. It‚Äôs not just me that this has happened to, it‚Äôs happened to a lot of people. This type of thing has happened to women, men. Sadly, at a certain point they begin to think that it‚Äôs normal. Or that it‚Äôs them. When it‚Äôs not.‚Äù
Plus, Johnny Depp suffered a major defeat in the British High Court last year when a judge ruled that it wasn‚Äôt libelous to describe him as a ‚Äúwife-beater‚Äù, but losing one battle isn‚Äôt the end of the war.
The big finale is coming in Fairfax County, Virginia in mid-2022, where he‚Äôs suing Amber Heard for $50M over a Washington Post op-ed she wrote about her experience as a victim of domestic vi*lence. We all remember that article, that Amber Heard wrote in 2018 for the Washington Post, and how Amber Heard was praised by many women first. Amber Heard even called herself a ‚Äòpublic figure representing domestic ab*se‚Äô and she said: ‚ÄòI feel the full force of our culture‚Äôs wrath for women who speak out‚Äô. Even though Johnny‚Äôs name wasn‚Äôt mentioned anywhere in Amber‚Äôs op-ed, it was not difficult to figure out who Amber was referring to. Plus, Amber Heard claimed to be a survivor of domestic abuse.
Since the article went viral, Johnny Depp has become an object of public hate and Johnny Depp lost some of his roles and his life was never the same. Well, Johnny Depp was not ready to be defeated and in 2019 Johnny Depp sued U.K. newspaper The Sun for referring to him in a story as a ‚Äúwife-beater.‚Äù And as it was already said, the judge found the paper‚Äôs claims to be substantially true, based largely on Amber Heard‚Äôs own testimony and JD lost the battle.  
However, JD also sued Amber Heard for $50 million for defamation over the article and this time celebs and even media outlets had already understood that Amber has been lying all this time and she‚Äôs not a victim at all. She is the one who made up a vicious plan to destroy Johnny Depp‚Äôs life. 

So, now I want to know your opinion. Do you think Amber Heard will win this time? Or she is going to fail and we all will celebrate Johnny Depp‚Äôs triumph? snippet.title: Amber Heard Is Now Facing Jail Time
snippet.description:
In 2015, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard got married. The two had met on the set of 2011‚Äôs The Rum Diary. A little more than a year after their marriage, Amber filed for divorce and began claiming that Johnny had been physically and verbally abusive to her during their short time together. Before much could come of it in court, Amber formally withdrew her claims. Her and Johnny came to a divorce settlement that saw Johnny paying out $7 million. Many following the situation saw this settlement as admittance of guilt on Johnny‚Äôs part. Such parties included UK publication The Sun.

Initially, there weren‚Äôt many consequences that came as a result of Amber‚Äôs allegations against her ex-husband. Johnny went forward with filming 2018‚Äôs Fantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald Franchise-runner JK Rowling personally defended Johnny whenever the press brought up the preceding divorce. However, a 2018 article published by The Sun reignited interest in Amber‚Äôs prior allegations against Johnny just a few months before the film was set to hit theaters. Although the film was still a success, Johnny‚Äôs future in Hollywood seemed tenuous. 

In 2018, Johnny Depp appeared in five films. In 2019, he appeared in only one. Now Johnny is suing Amber for libel and defamation as a result of the damage that her allegations have done on his career. Join Trender as we explore why Amber Heard is now facing jail time.
